  "prompt": "Why isn't Anime popular in India?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why anime hasn't gained widespread popularity in India:\n\n1. Cultural differences\n- Japanese storytelling and cultural references might seem unfamiliar\n- Less exposure to anime compared to Western media\n\n2. Limited accessibility\n- Historically, anime was not easily available\n- Limited dubbing in local languages\n- Fewer dedicated streaming platforms\n\n3. Perception issues\n- Often viewed as children's content\n- Misunderstood as just cartoons\n- Less awareness about diverse anime genres\n\n4. Strong local entertainment industry\n- Bollywood and regional film industries dominate entertainment\n- Indian animation and TV shows are more prevalent\n\n5. Language barriers\n- Most anime is in Japanese with subtitles\n- Not as convenient for casual viewers\n\n6. Cost of access\n- Anime merchandise and legal streaming can be expensive\n- Piracy is less developed compared to other regions\n\nHowever, the situation is changing:\n- Increased internet penetration\n- Growing youth interest in global pop culture\n- Platforms like Netflix and Amazon Prime introducing anime\n- Growing anime fan communities in metropolitan cities\n\nWhile anime isn't mainstream in India, its popularity is gradually increasing, especially among younger, urban audiences interested in global entertainment.",
